omplete worksheet problems applying these concepts and submit your answers with clear steps.\n\n**Grading Rubric:**  \n- Demonstration of graph transformations (30%)  \n- Correct function combinations and calculations (30%)  \n- Finding inverses accurately (30%)  \n- Clear explanations and work shown (10%)  \n\n---\n\n### Week 3: Quadratic Functions and Polynomial Review\n**Topics Covered:**  \n- Quadratic Functions  \n- Polynomials of Higher Degree  \n- Zeros of Polynomials  \n\n**Instructions:**  \n1. Review graphing quadratics and their properties like vertex, intercepts, and axis of symmetry.  \n2. Understand higher-degree polynomial functions and their behavior.  \n3. Practice finding zeros of polynomials algebraically and graphically.  \n4. Submit completed exercises with detailed solutions.\n\n**Grading Rubric:**  \n- Accurate graphing and interpretation of quadratics (40%)  \n- Correct analysis of polynomial graphs and zeros (40%)  \n- Completeness and clarity of solutions (20%)  \n\n---\n\n### Week 4: Trigonometry Basics and the Unit Circle\n**Topics Covered:**  \n- Radian and Degree Measure  \n- The Unit Circle  \n- Right Triangle Trigonometry  \n\n**Instructions:**  \n1. Learn to convert between degrees and radians and understand their applications.  \n2. Study the unit circle, including key angles in both degrees and radians, and their sine, cosine, and tangent values.  \n3. Practice solving right triangle problems using trigonometric ratios.  \n4. Complete and submit worksheet problems on these topics.\n\n**Grading Rubric:**  \n- Accuracy in conversions between degrees and radians (25%)  \n- Correct identification of unit circle values (35%)  \n- Successful application of trig ratios in right triangles (30%)  \n- Presentation and explanation of answers (10%)  \n\n---\n\n### Week 5: Trigonometric Functions and Graphs\n**Topics Covered:**  \n- Graphs of Sine and Cosine  \n- Other Trigonometric Functions  \n- Applications and Models  \n\n**Instructions:** 